<item>
            <title>[SPR-7972] RestTemplate.putFor*</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-7972</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the PUT methods on RestTemplate are void. I&apos;m aware that in typical scenarios PUT does not return any value, but there are some cases where methods putForObject and/or putForEntity are required.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Prime example is connectivity with Apache CouchDB that return revision number of the document when updating the document using PUT method.&lt;br/&gt;
More details can be seen here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.apache.org/couchdb/HTTP_Document_API#PUT&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://wiki.apache.org/couchdb/HTTP_Document_API#PUT&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="36395">SPR-7972</key>
